# em_lca.cpp must be compiled without floating-point contraction (no FMA
# fusing of a*b + c) so that the C++ EM core reproduces the reference R
# implementations in R/em_algorithm.R and R/constraints.R bit-for-bit:
# R always rounds each product before accumulating, and fused multiply-adds
# would otherwise differ in the last bits and let EM trajectories diverge.
# The flag is scoped to em_lca.o (GNU make target-specific variable) so the
# pre-existing conjoint-sampler sources keep their original flags.
em_lca.o: PKG_CXXFLAGS += -ffp-contract=off
